{{Infobox person |image = |caption = |name = Vijay Goel |birth_place = [[Bareilly]] in UP |known_for = Leader of the Trade Delegation Team accompanying UK Deputy Prime Minister [[Nick Clegg]]'s 1 st ever visit to India in 2015. Charter Member & Former Board Member of "[[TiE]]" |occupation = Attorney |boards = Centenary Ambassador' of [[SOAS]] |education = Business Law & Tax (LL.B, and a Post Graduate Diploma in Business Analytics (PGDBA) |spouse = Poonam Goel |website = {{URL|www.vijaygoel.co.uk}} |footnotes = }}
'''Vijay Goel''' (born September 29, 1974) is a UK-based attorney, [[corporate lawyer]] and senior partner for the London office of Singhania & Co. Goel received a [[Bachelor of law]] in Business Law & Tax (LL.B, and a Post Graduate Diploma in Business Analytics (PGDBA), Lucknow in 1998. Goel was awarded from Indian finance minister Mr.[[Arun Jaitley|Arun jaitly]] in year 2015. He has expertise in advising clients on matters relating to corporate law, laws relating to joint ventures and foreign collaborations. He has expertise in real estate transactions and has completed some major real estate transactions in India and Former Advisor on [[Emerging Markets]] to Rt. Honorable [[Nick Clegg]] MP, Former Deputy Prime Minister of UK.
==Early life==
Vijay was born in [[Bareilly]] in [[Uttar Pradesh]], to Mr G N Goel and mother Late Usha Goel. He completed his schooling in village called Tikunia Kheri in UP and then moved to Lucknow, capital of UP for Higher Education. From childhood, he used to look after his father's business in Tikunia kheri in UP. Vijay was a bright student he has done B com, MBA and LLB from [[lucknow]]. Later moved to Delhi in 1998 and joined Singhania & Co and now settled in London with his wife Poonam Goel and son Arav Goel.
==Achievements and contributions==
Vijay has won many awards including the law day award from the [[President of India]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=India|first1=Press Trust of|title=NRI lawyer felicitated in UK|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/nri-lawyer-felicitated-in-uk-114021200724_1.html|work=Business Standard India|date=12 February 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Mr. Vijay Goel- London Based NRI Bags the India's National Law Day Award|url=http://www.indiaprwire.com/pressrelease/other/2009112438201.htm|work=www.indiaprwire.com}}</ref> In recognition for Vijay's role in promoting judicial reforms in India. Mr.[[KG Balakrishnan|K.G.Balakrishnan]], [[Chief Justice of India]] honoured Vijay Goel with a Memento
Vijay is the Ambassador of [[Barnardo's]], UK's largest and Oldest national children's charity.
Vijay was conferred Asian Voice Asian Achievers Award for 'Professional of the Year' by Britain's minister of state for Justice Lord [[Tom McNally]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Vijay Goel receives Asian Achievers 'Award for Professional of the Year' {{!}} Latest News & Updates at Daily News & Analysis|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-vijay-goel-receives-asian-achievers-award-for-professional-of-the-year-1448896|work=dna|date=7 October 2010}}</ref> Vijay was awarded 'Asian Leadership in Europe' by Asian Who's Who International at a Gala ceremony held at the [[Dorchester Hotel]], Park Lane, London on 30 November 2009. The award was presented by Lord [[Karan Bilimoria]]<ref>{{cite news|last1=Bench|first1=Bar &|title=Vijay Goel wins Asian Leadership in Europe Award - Bar & Bench|url=http://barandbench.com/vijay-goel-wins-asian-leadership-europe-award/|work=Bar & Bench|date=1 December 2009}}</ref> <ref>{{cite news|last1=Rao/PTI|first1=H. S.|title=NRI gets leadership award for promoting Indian culture|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/economy-policy/nri-gets-leadership-award-for-promoting-indian-culture-109120100139_1.html|work=Business Standard India|date=1 December 2009}}</ref> Vijay was the Coordinator of a high level delegation of the [[Commonwealth Business Council]], UK for the Government of Gujarat for its Vibrant Gujarat Summit in January 2009.
